ad_creative_body:
New Ulster Unionist Party leader Steve Aiken standing in East Antrim 

New Ulster Unionist Party Leader Dr Steve Aiken OBE MLA has been nominated as his party‚Äôs candidate for the General Election in East Antrim.

The 57-year-old, who lives in the constituency, served 31 years in the Royal Navy during which time he commanded nuclear submarines, was made an OBE and was awarded the US Meritorious Service Medal for his military service in the Middle East.   Since his retirement from the Service Steve has been a CEO, before becoming an MLA for neighbouring South Antrim in 2016. 

Steve said:
‚ÄúIt is an enormous privilege to be selected to be the Ulster Unionist candidate in the forthcoming Westminster election.  As well as living in the constituency, I have strong connections with East Antrim - having been educated at Belfast High School, learned to sail at Carrickfergus Sailing Club, with strong family connections to Carrick, and believe strongly it is time that we have a change in who represents us at Westminster.

‚ÄúWe need to give East Antrim the chance to elect an MP who will put the Union first, fight Boris Johnson‚Äôs withdrawal deal and stand up for all the people of East Antrim; regardless of religion, identity, gender or class.

‚ÄúI am standing in East Antrim because I believe in leading from the front.  I want to challenge the sitting MP on policy- and be in no doubt that it was his and the DUP‚Äôs reckless policy which has led to the current mess where the rest of the UK is set to leave the EU with Northern Ireland left behind in a constitutional limbo.

‚ÄúNever has a General Election been more important.  With the outcome so uncertain, it is essential that East Antrim returns an MP who will fight to stop Boris‚Äôs Withdrawal Deal, - who won‚Äôt succumb to the folly of putting a border down the Irish Sea, who will not vote to cap Nurses pay and who will enact legislation to fight the climate emergency-rather than deny its very existence.  

‚ÄúThe Ulster Unionist Party voted, on balance, to remain in the referendum. As a democratic party we recognised the result of that referendum.  However, as a unionist party, right now with Boris Johnson‚Äôs withdrawal deal being the only one on the table, we have to recognise a clear fact ‚Äì if the Conservatives‚Äô deal goes through, Northern Ireland will, well and truly, become a ‚Äòplace apart‚Äô.

‚ÄúI offer pro-Union voters a choice.  A choice between an Ulster Unionist candidate who will offer a positive, progressive vision for unionism, protecting our place within the United Kingdom and the sitting DUP MP who has dropped the ball, allowing a border to be put up the Irish Sea and whose party has dragged the reputation of unionism into the gutter.

‚ÄúWhat drives me is doing what‚Äôs best for my constituents, and trying to make Northern Ireland work again.  We can only do that by changing who represents us at Parliament, and I‚Äôm asking the people of East Antrim to come out and vote for me on the 12th December as the only person who can make that change happen.‚Äù

John Stewart Roy Beggs Keith James Turner Maureen Morrow Andrew Wilson Steve Aiken OBE MLA

'Those election promises'

The UK has just embarked on yet another general election. Once again, the airwaves are full of promises with political parties pledging to spend billions on education, healthcare, and housing. But in a world now dominated by ‚Äòfake news‚Äô we‚Äôre deeply cynical that once the election is over many of them will be forgotten. But maybe we have reason to be more hopeful.

In 2017 a study of 12 European and North American nations found that parties elected to office were likely to fulfil their campaign promises to a considerable extent.

In a similar way it‚Äôs all too easy to be dismissive of the church and cynical about the Good News that Christians are supposed to represent. But listen to these words from Jesus in a declaration about why he had come, ‚ÄòThe Spirit of the Lord is on me‚Ä¶ to preach good news to the poor‚Ä¶ proclaim freedom for prisoners‚Ä¶ recovery of sight for the blind‚Ä¶ release for the oppressed.‚Äô During his life on earth Jesus fulfilled these promises in every way.

Politicians will come and go, making and breaking promises, and then disappearing into history. Jesus, on the other hand, has been keeping his promises for 2,000 years and always will.

www.turn-the-page.co.uk

You can listen to this story and many others by subscribing to the Turn The Page podcast in iTunes

Statement:

'Boris' Brexit Breakthrough?'

The Alex Salmond Show examines the final countdown to #Brexit and finds that if Boris Johnson can square the DUP he might carry Parliament to support a soft Brexit for Ireland and a hard Brexit for Britain. But will this potential deal to leave the European Union result in the breakup of the union of Great Britain and Northern Ireland?

Britain's main opposition Labour Party cannot support the Brexit deal agreed on Thursday (October 17) between the European Union and the British government, its leader Jeremy Corbyn said.

"As it stands we cannot support this deal ... also it is unclear whether it has the support of his allies in the DUP, or indeed, many allies on his own backbenchers," he said.

Asked whether he would put forward a motion of no-confidence to try to bring down Prime Minister Boris Johnson during a planned extraordinary session in parliament on Saturday, Corbyn said the weekend was a time to discuss the Brexit deal and other issues would be for next week.

WESTMINSTER - (Bywire News) Prime Minister Boris Johnson said on Thursday that Britain and the European Union had agreed a "great" new Brexit deal but still faced resistance from the Northern Irish Democratic Unionist Party (DUP) as he sought support for the deal.

Britain and the European Union have been racing to renegotiate the Withdrawal Agreement in time for an Oct. 31 Brexit, but the deal still needs approval from parliament.

"We've got a great new deal that takes back control," Johnson said in a tweet.

"Now parliament should get Brexit done on Saturday so we can move on to other priorities like the cost of living, the NHS, violent crime and our environment."

However, the DUP, who have expressed concerns that the Brexit deal could cut Northern Ireland off from Britain in customs and regulatory terms, said there had been no change in their position following the confirmation of the deal.

Earlier the DUP had said it could not support the last-ditch Brexit proposal due to concerns about the issues of customs and consent, adding there was a lack of clarity on VAT (sales tax) arrangements.

As Boris does his best to crash out of Europe, with the help of the DUP, there could be a Westminster election coming very soon.

In Fermanagh South Tyrone there is only one anti-brexit candidate who can win - Michelle Gildernew MP.

If you're not on the electoral register apply today through the following link;

http://www.eoni.org.uk/Register-To-Vote/Register-to-vote-change-address-change-name

Join us on Tuesday 1st October at Old Court (basement) in St Leonard's Road Windsor from 7.30pm where we have Peter Stefanovic coming to talk to us.  This is a free to attend event but as we had to hire the room we will have a change collection.  

Peter Stefanovic is a high profile Lawyer, straight-talking Journalist, blogger, Filmmaker, campaigner, Labour supporter and Political and Social Commentator widely known for his no nonsense films debunking Political deceit.

He has a weekly post reach of over 10 million people. Stefanovic is a former Partner at national Law Firm Simpson Millar LLP. Heralded as one of the UK's most successful Clinical Negligence Lawyers Stefanovic was nominated for Legal Personality of the Year in 2016. He is a champion for social Justice and the NHS. He is a columnist in THE WORD Newspaper and regularly appears on television and radio. His video reaction to Laura Kuenssberg (March 2017) was watched by 1.3 Million People in 48 hours. His 2 films responding to the U.K Governments confidence and supply agreement with the DUP were watched over 5 million times in a week. Stefanovic's films and Political commentaries have had over 20 million views in the past year alone

ad_creative_body:
*Press Statement

*Alliance Party selects Bradshaw to contest South Belfast having emerged as largest party in May*
 
The Alliance Party has selected local MLA Paula Bradshaw to contest the South Belfast constituency at the Westminster election as it seeks to build on its status as the largest Remain party in the constituency at this year‚Äôs elections.
 
Ms Bradshaw stated: ‚ÄúThe Alliance Party emerged over 2000 votes clear of any other Remain party in the South Belfast constituency at May‚Äôs local election. Naomi Long‚Äôs victory at the subsequent European Election further demonstrated that we are best placed to build the necessary range of support across the whole constituency to unseat the DUP. Since May, we have double the elected representation of any other Remain party.
 
‚ÄúThis cannot be a tired old Nationalist versus Unionist election. This election must be United Community against Brexit. This is one reason I am proud to designate ‚ÄòUnited Community‚Äô in the Assembly.‚Äù
 
‚ÄúI will also be standing on the Alliance Party reputation for hard work and delivery right across the constituency. On issues ranging from the availability of cancer drugs to HPV vaccines, the Alliance Party in South Belfast has shown an ability not just to talk about things, but to get things done, which have a real impact on people‚Äôs daily lives.
 
‚ÄúSouth Belfast is also an overwhelmingly Remain constituency which is why it swung so heavily behind Alliance at the European Elections. The choice before the public is simple. If they simply do the same the same thing they did in May and vote Alliance, they will elect a United Community Remain MP representative of the whole constituency.‚Äù

Speaking in support of Paula, Alliance Leader Naomi Long MEP said: ‚ÄúIt was clear in May that Alliance has a unique ability to reach across the community, and that by voting Alliance you can get people elected at all levels you represent your views.

‚ÄúI want to tell people in South Belfast that there can be no better person to do that than Paula Bradshaw. You have seen how hard she has worked and the real change she has delivered even without a sitting Assembly, putting shoe leather on the ground and getting your problems solved.

‚ÄúWith Paula‚Äôs focus on detail and her expertise in all areas relevant to Brexit, with two relevant degrees and two decades‚Äô worth of work in and for the community covering the key regulations and funding which will be affected by our future relationship with the EU, I am saying to the people of South Belfast there can be no better person to represent you and to turn up and ensure your interests are protected.

‚ÄúIt is clear the Alliance surge is continuing. So I urge you to get behind Paula and her Alliance team the way you got behind Alliance in May, and you will deliver the same result.‚Äù

There's a chance to stop #Brexit in the coming Westminster election. Alasdair McDonnell recognises just how important that is.

Claire Hanna is South Belfast's best bet to take out the DUP. Time for Remainers to unite.
ad_creative_link_description: Former SDLP leader Dr Alasdair McDonnell has withdrawn from the race to be his party‚Äôs South Belfast candidate in the next Westminster election.

Unprecedented, historic scenes in the House last night. Johnson‚Äôs prorogation of parliament at such a crucial time in our history is a tragic act of folly equal to anything Charles I came up with, an act of the most abject cowardice and an insult to our intelligence as a nation. 

But the opposition have played an absolute blinder. As a student of politics it was wonderful to see the legislature seize power from the executive, turn Johnson‚Äôs planned massive, rampant election into an impotent flop and force him to either get a deal or ask the E.U. for an extension.  

In my opinion neither of these were in Cummings‚Äô plans at all: if the law is adhered to and the Brexit communications revealed, I predict they will reveal strategy for an election framed as ‚Äòparliament versus the people‚Äô straddling a chaotic no-deal crash out  - with all the blame shoved onto Johnny Foreigner of course.  

This is now on the back burner and the ball is in Johnson‚Äôs  court. His massive hubris led him to believe Cummings would be able to play Parliament for fools and the strategy would work, but it‚Äôs been torpedoed. Now he has the choice between finding a deal, going cap in hand to Brussels to ask for an extension or breaking the law. 

So what will happen now? Do remember that Johnson‚Äôs lack of principle makes Niccolo Machiavelli look like Thomas Paine, as the infamous pro-Remain essay bears witness. He doesn‚Äôt actually believe in anything at all apart from what is best for Boris Johnson. So my prediction is that he will change tack and go for a deal, with an election message to follow claiming credit for ending the crisis, and since the DUP are out of the equation now he‚Äôs lost his majority I predict he‚Äôll go for the Northern Ireland only backstop option. 

It‚Äôs not unlikely that at the  eleventh hour some kind of deal will be stitched together and we‚Äôll leave the EU without literally falling off the White Cliffs of Dover on October 31st. The alternatives - dying in a ditch, asking for an extension or going to jail - will not appeal to the studiedly scruffy egomaniac one bit.

In that circumstance small businesses, people reliant on medicines, travelling musicians like myself and everyone apart from the large but minority cohort of 50 plus tabloid engendered irrationality addicts  (I‚Äôll avoid the meat-related cliche) will breathe a sigh of relief. 

Then comes the election. Johnson will lay claim to the title of national saviour, the Brexit Party and DUP will scream ‚Äòbetrayal‚Äô but probably won‚Äôt stand against him despite everything they have said for fear of splitting the vote and letting JC in, and aided by the mainstream media a lot of people will give Johnson credit for ‚Äòdelivering Brexit‚Äô.  

That is where I predict we‚Äôll end up in a few weeks. I may well be wrong, of course, but having weighed up all the alternatives, there you are. 

Whether it is this scenario or virtually any other, though, it is my ABSOLUTE CONVICTION that if the anti Johnson vote is split between Labour, Greens, Lib Dem‚Äôs, Plaid and Scottish Nats JOHNSON WILL WIN. His entire strategy is facing a divided opposition. In order to defeat him the opposition must pursue the same strategy in the country as they just have in Parliament and stand ONE candidate against the Tories in every seat. 

To those who say the Lib Dem‚Äôs are a bunch of untrustworthy, opportunistic con artists I say I fully agree. But I‚Äôd rather be in coalition with Arfur Daley than be governed by Oswald Mosley. 

Mark my words, if Johnson wins the next election we will have the most right wing government in our history. And those who put party loyalties before defeating that are, in my view, totally misguided. Conventional politics is over.

Boris‚Äôs Secret Diary. August 8th. 
14.00. 
Cummings on the front page of most papers again. I don‚Äôt get it, I‚Äôm the photogenic one, I still have my golden locks, thanks to L‚ÄôOreal. It‚Äôs a mystery why he‚Äôs photographed so much, he‚Äôs got a head like a bowling ball. Whenever I see him I feel like sticking two fingers up his nose and my thumb in his ear.
15.12
Couldn‚Äôt have Penny Mordaunt in the Cabinet because I don‚Äôt think she fancies me. Whereas Liz Truss has that permanent twinkle that says ‚ÄúYour place or mine?‚Äù
16.34
How things have changed, once if you told proven whoppers like my ¬£350m per week for the NHS and the one Mordaunt and Gove kept trotting out about Turkey joining the EU you would be crucified. Now nobody gives a toss, we won and everyone loves a winner. 
17.45
It was Cummings who thought of the two big whoppers and his pals at Cambridge Analytica who spread the word in targeted social media ads. Pure genius. It‚Äôs a wonder that we didn‚Äôt win by more. 
17.50
We gave the DUP a billion to get them on side. After Brexit we may have to give a billion to the IRA to stop them from bombing London again. As long as they stick to Ireland that‚Äôs OK, we can do business. 
18.01
As the Prince of Denmark says. ‚ÄúO God, I could be bounded in a nutshell and count myself a king of infinite space, were it not that I have bad dreams.‚Äù I dreamed I was naked, and lubed up from tip to toe, falling down an ever narrowing tube, in the knowledge that eventually I‚Äôd be stuck no matter how oily I was.
18.12. 
Crikey just remembered another dream. The Great Unwashed all around the world suddenly came to the realisation that Multinationals and billionaires don‚Äôt pay tax and they‚Äôre also the ones who own the fossil fuels, banks, armaments and meat companies. So they marched for change in every city around the world. Horrible, Horrible!

The Government have a majority of 3 ! 
650 parliamentary seats - 1 Vacant - 1 Speaker - 7 Sinn Fein (who don‚Äôt take up their position) = 641
Conservative & DUP = 322 
With a by election, rumoured defections and plenty of Tory remainer rebels there‚Äôs a general election coming soon

Boris Johnson, ‚ÄúDo or die!‚Äù ( As long as it‚Äôs the Irish who die. )
Theresa May wanted a compromise. The ERG were greedy and wanted it all, so they brought her crashing down. They don‚Äôt want the Irish border safeguard known as ‚ÄúThe backstop‚Äù. They would rather regurgitate ‚ÄúThe Troubles‚Äù, why?

The backstop means we stay in the EU indefinitely as there‚Äôs no alternative without breaking the Good Friday Agreement. We can‚Äôt do a trade deal until we agree to the backstop. 

In 2015, Conservative, UKIP and DUP MEPs unsuccessfully voted against the EU‚Äôs plans to crack down on corporate tax avoidance, by making companies report where they make their profits and pay taxes. 

Do you think it‚Äôs a coincidence that the three parties who encourage tax avoidance for the rich are also the Brexit Parties?

THESE ARE THE 15 BENEFICIARIES OF BREXIT.

(1) The ERG, a bunch of tax dodging, flag waving, tub thumping Tory throwbacks who still believe that Britannia rules the waves, and are still fighting WW2. 
(2) Those who want to escape the EU‚Äôs new ‚ÄúTax Avoidance Directive‚Äù. International banks, accounting and law firms and those who use our many tax havens. 
(3)The Koch brothers, fossil fuels billionaires who back Donald Trump and want to convince us that climate change is just Project Fear. 
(4) Psychopath and richest man in the world, Vladimir Putin. He wants to break up the EU and add the weaker countries to his circle of influence. 
(5) Aaron Banks pays for climate change denier Nigel Farage to prize us away from Europe. Like Salvini in Italy and Orban in Hungary, Banks has links to Russia. 
(6) The Telegraph, Sun, Daily Mail and Express. Their billionaire owners like Murdoch and the Barclay Brothers register their newspapers and other companies in tax havens. 
(7) Drug cartels, kleptocrats, Russian oligarchs, the Mafia and other criminals who use London property and our tax havens to launder money. 
(8) Corbyn‚Äôs Office were obstructive to Labour‚Äôs ‚ÄúStronger In‚Äù team during the Referendum. They don‚Äôt want the EU interfering in their plan to nationalise literally everything. 
(9) Importers like Dyson, Wetherspoon‚Äôs and JCB. Their no deal plan means crippling tariffs for exporters but zero tariffs for importers like them. 
(10) Investors in Emerging Markets like Mogg who‚Äôs company Somerset Capital Investments (Cayman & Singapore) usefully have their assets in dollars, essential for when the pound falls again after Brexit. 
(11) The American tech giants we all use, make billions but pay no tax. 
(12) The old National Front, English Defence League, Britain First and other racist groups who now vote UKIP and for the Brexit Party. 
(13) Robert Mercer the tech billionaire who backs Trump. They want to cut the U.K. away from Europe and give us an America First trade deal,  taking over our NHS in exchange for chlorinated chicken etc.
(14) Sports personalities, film and music stars plus other high earners who are groomed by accountant and law firms to send their earnings off shore to avoid tax. 
(15) The DUP who you would think would campaign to Remain to avoid the Backstop. They have twice been given ¬£1bn to vote with the Tories, plus they had ¬£430,000 mysteriously appear in their bank account for ads in London newspapers supporting Leave. They refuse to admit where this money came from.

An article in today's Metro Newspaper from our Director on Westminster's historic vote, and the hard work that comes next for our community. 
"61 per cent of LGBTQ+ young people in N. Ireland have had suicide ideation with 25 per cent having actually attempted suicide. For the first time they do not live under an establishment which says ‚Äòyou are not equal‚Äô. Or ‚Äòrepulsive‚Äô, or ‚Äòvile‚Äô, or ‚Äòan abomination‚Äô to quote just a few of the DUP‚Äôs public pronouncements. For the first time those precious young lives live under an establishment which says ‚ÄòYou are equal. You are valued. You are loved‚Äô. What better message to send them on the 50th anniversary of the Stonewall riots?"
